We scaled past $6.5M in ARR with Instantly.ai powering ~70% of our cold email sending.

Here are my 5 biggest learnings sending millions of emails:

1. Lead with value

Most cold emailers try to gain something from their recipients: 

"can I ask 15 min of your time?"
"can I pick your brain on {topic}?‚Äù

The best cold emailers give.

Here‚Äôs how I do so:

I picture myself signing these leads as clients.
And I think about the first thing I‚Äôd do for them if I were to sign them.

Then I do it.
For free.

For example: 

I ran a campaign targeting recruiting firms.

I figured the first thing I‚Äôd do for them would be to build a list of HR Directors at orgs hiring for 10+ roles.

So, I built the list.¬†
I sent it to them. 

And I attached a tutorial on how they could build it too.

This got me way more leads than I knew what to do with.


2. Nail your messaging for 1 person.

Every novice cold emailer is obsessed with scale.

They ideate strategies and don‚Äôt bother with them if they don‚Äôt see a clear path to scale.

With cold emailing, it looks like so:

- They build a huge list.
- Think about messaging that will appeal to everyone.
- & realise that appealing to everyone = appealing to no one.

Here‚Äôs what I do:

- I build a list of ~20 people who are a perfect fit.
- I write every single message by hand. 

When you craft these messages manually, you uncover patterns that most miss...

which are data points you can leverage later on to scale.


3. Your lead list is your biggest lever to success.

Novice cold emailers spend too much time thinking about what to write.
And too little time thinking about who they should reach out to.

But,¬†
Sending your message to the right person > sending a nicely crafted message.

You want to identify people struggling with a problem you can solve.
When you do that, the message writes itself. 

E.g: we ran campaigns for an HR SaaS company that helps with employee churn. 

We looked for targets with poor Glassdoor reviews and low employee tenure.

If both were true, we assumed these companies were a good fit.


4. Deliverability is king

Good deliverability doesn't equate success.
Bad deliverability guarantees your cold email campaigns will fail.

In our case, we make sure to do:

- Warm-up emails
- Secondary domains
- No open rate tracking
- Set up SPF, DKIM, DMARC
- Send < 30 emails/day per mailbox

... and, most importantly, sending emails we‚Äôd like to receive.


5. Reply to interested leads ASAP.

Replying fast = a bigger proportion of meetings from your positive replies.

Most cold emailers boast positive replies as a success metric.
That‚Äôs actually when the real work begins.

‚Üí Note: Instantly released AI reply agents that monitor & draft personalised replies on your behalf. They can run entirely on autopilot... or with a human in the loop.
